BeitEnactedbytheSenateandHouseofRepresentativesinGeneralCourtconvened:
1 1 New Paragraphs; Definitions. Amend RSA 437:1 by inserting after paragraph V the following
2 newparagraphs:
3 VI. "Residential breeder" means an individual who owns and breeds dogs or cats within
4 their primary residence and not in a separate breeding facility. A residential breeder's operations
5 shall be integrated intotheir home environment and shall transfer no morethan50 dogs and/or cats
6 with or without a fee or donation, between January 1 and December 31 of any calendar year A
7 residential breeder shall raise the litters in the household setting by maintaining the animals as
8 part of the family environment. A residential breeder shall not import animals for transfer with or
9 withoutafee.
10 VII. "Importedanimal"meanstheoffspringofanyanimalwhichwasimportedintothestate
11 while pregnant. Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter, any animal imported prior to
12 birth shall be considered to have met the requirements for importation if the pregnant female has
13 mettherequirementsforimportation.
14 2 EffectiveDate. Thisactshalltakeeffect60daysafteritspassage.

